And this morning Kiev confirmed that "Mosca attacks "civil infrastructure and people," &nbsp;" in Sumy, a Russian drone Shahed hit a hospital." "The leaders - the White House has explained in an account of the call - have agreed that the path towards peace will begin with a ceasefire energy and infrastructural, as well as with technical negotiations on the implementation of a ceasefire marine in the Black Sea, a ceasefire complete and a permanent peace".
During the interview Trump and Putin agreed that a better "bilateral relationship" between the US and Russia will help global economic growth and geopolitical stability, with "enormous economic agreements» on the horizon. The two leaders then sent a message to Iran on nuclear power: "It should never be in the position to destroy Israel."
The warning is also a clear indication: the two countries will address the issue of the proliferation of strategic weapons, but it is not clear how far this commitment can go.
Negotiations in Saudi Arabia will continue and will have to give further answers in a short time. Putin, to confirm the value of the call, ordered the army to suspend attacks on Ukrainian energy infrastructure. The Russian president, according to what the Kremlin said, however, asked the "complete termination" of weapons supplies in Kiev and the sharing of intelligence information. The Russian President also informed Trump of an exchange of 175 prisoners >for part with Ukraine and should be completed tomorrow.
<h2>Zelensky: Putin is not ready to finish the war</h2>
Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky said that the conditions placed by his Russian counterpart Vladimir Putin for a truce with Kiev aim to "debt" Ukraine and demonstrate that it is not ready to "end" war. "All his game is to weaken us as much as possible", said Zelensky in an online press conference after the telephone conversation between Vladimir Putin and Donald Trump. In particular, the Russian President called for the end of Western aid to Ukraine.&nbsp;
<h2>Berlin after Russian raids, Putin tregua is not serious</h2>
Germany accused Putin of "playing" after Kiev reported Russian attacks on Ukrainian civil infrastructure a few hours after Moscow agreed to temporarily suspend the raid on energy structures. "We saw that the attacks on civil infrastructure did not at all diminish in the first night after this allegedly revolutionary and grandiose call" between Putin and US President Donald Trump, said German Defense Minister Boris Pistorius in a television interview.
<h2>Trump, with Putin we have not talked about military aid in Kiev</h2>
U.S. President Donald Trump denied the Kremlin statements that Vladimir Putin would call for complete cessation of military aid and intelligence supplies in Kiev during their phone call yesterday. "No, (Putin) didn't ask for anything, we didn't talk about aid. We talked about many things, but not aids," Trump replied to Fox News, who asked him to confirm the information that came from Moscow.&nbsp;
